begin_memory_text: He was nice, it was a little difficult to get started. I didn't ask questions that were open-ended enough to get him going so we didn't stick on anything.
middle_memory_text: We talked a little bit about his brother and his brother's work and his own work. His brother went to school at OU where my family went so we chatted about that a bit.
end_memory_text: We finally hit on the topic that excited him- his geo-hiking and his travel to haunted houses. It was quite fascinating and he talked about places and experiences that I'd never heard of before. It is something that he and his dad do together and really seem to enjoy.
rest_of_day_open: It will be quite busy with a lot of work and a lot of projects around the house. Staying home as much as I have has given me a lot of time to clearly see how many projects I have been putting off and it's a good time to knock them out so that I'm ready to roll when things open up.
critical_positive: I found that he didn't really want to hear about me so I focused on him. The first questions directed to/about him didn't really resonate but once I asked him what he had been doing for fun during Covid, he lit up. That's when he started talking about the things that interested him and they were quite interesting.
critical_negative: You can tell that he's a nice guy but not a warm-fuzzy sort and I suspect a bit of an introvert. So my questioning that has worked well previously did not work with him. There were some awkward pauses and I wasn't sure where to go, finding myself making idle chit-chat.

begin_memory_text: We talked about where we live. She lives in Dallas, Texas, but used to live up near Chicago. I told her about where I resided and the weather that was hitting us at the moment.
middle_memory_text: We talked about family members. She spoke about her mom and the difficult situation she was having with her. I talked about my brother and his time in college
end_memory_text: We talked about hobbies. I mentioned Geocaching, but we ended the conversation talking about haunted houses. I spoke about my trips to various places out of state and my experiences in them.
rest_of_day_open: It should go pretty well. I have already finished a lot of work I had to get done for my job and my health issues seem to be improving a bit. I am going to be reading a lot more of various books as well as listening to some great music.
critical_positive: Pretty much everything went very well. We hit it off immediately. She was very nice and friendly. We did not talk over each other very much. The conversation went from topic to topic spending just enough time on each one. We both learned some interesting stuff about each other and ourselves.
critical_negative: I cannot really think of very many things that did not work well in the conversation I just had. There was one or two awkward pauses, but we breezed right past those like they didn't even happen. The beginning took maybe a minute to get going, but once it did, nothing but smooth sailing from then on.
